            <thetext>The navigation list in the Website API Viewer takes a long time to render (tested with IE11/Win8.1 on a Dell XPS convertible). This can be a problem if the app is loaded with a URL hash. In that case, the user might click an internal link in the content before the list is ready. The content will scroll to the list target, then when the list is done it scrolls to the target from the URL hash, which can be confusing.

We should try to either speed up list rendering, or at least deactivate the UI (perhaps using a blocker) until it&#39;s ready.</thetext>
